07/10/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic called a meeting of cabinet members and heads of key financial control institutions Monday (6 October), withthe goal of stepping up measures against organised crime. 
Mikerevic called for improved co-operation among state control bodies and other institutions charged with financial and economic functions. 
Attending the meeting were representatives of the trade and tourism ministry, the interior ministry and the finance ministry, as well as the tax and customs administration. 
(SRNA, FENA - 06/10/03)
